The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Monday, April 21, 2003  Good Morning Hello It's Monday, April 21, 2003				 																Roads to avoid				 																																	Strand Road, Kingsway, Rani Rashmoni Road, Red Road and Mayo Road, from 9 am. Members of the Lodha community to congregate.				 																																	Chowringhee, opposite Metro cinema, from 3.30 pm. Ganatantrik Mahila Samity of the CPM to stage a rally.				 																Poetry				 																																	A poetry-reading session with Sunil Gangopadhyay, Dibyendu Palit, Nabanita Dev Sen and others will be held alongside an art exhibition by Sudhangsu at Alliance Francaise de Calcutta from 10 am to 6 pm. Film-maker Goutam Ghose will inaugurate the exhibition at 6.30 pm.				 																Music				 																																	A classical vocal recital by Sandipan Samajpati at Seagull Arts amp; Media Resource Centre from 6 pm. Writer Amit Chaudhuri will introduce the session.				 																Posters				 																																	50 years of French Posters (1940 to 2000), in memory of graphic designer Savignac, at Birla Academy of Art and Culture.				 																Science				 																																	An exhibition on the 25th anniversary of National Council of Science Museums at Birla Industrial amp; Technological Museum.				 																Art watch				 																																	An exhibition of paintings by women artists of Gond and Bhil tribes, presented by Srijan, at Sriniketan Art Gallery, Sodepur. 				 																																	A tryst with the river, an exhibition of drawings presented by Sea Explorers Institute, at Artists Circle Gallery, 2 pm-8 pm.
